  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n`OVM_L1CrossDomainMessenger` re-encoded the `xDomainCalldata` in `replayMessage` function. \r\n\r\nIn `replayMessage`:\r\n- `transactionHash` is [computed with the `_message` param](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/e23b26430b7252057abc800a134d8484af14f917/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/bridge/messaging/OVM_L1CrossDomainMessenger.sol#L322) so the `_message` param [has to be an encoded `xDomainCalldata`](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/e23b26430b7252057abc800a134d8484af14f917/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/bridge/messaging/OVM_L1CrossDomainMessenger.sol#L216)\r\n- but this `_message` is [encoded again](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/e23b26430b7252057abc800a134d8484af14f917/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/bridge/messaging/OVM_L1CrossDomainMessenger.sol#L331-L336) before sending the message\r\n- so this results in `replayMessage` sending a re-encoded `xDomainCalldata` like this:\r\n```\r\nrelayMessage(\r\n    ...,\r\n    relayMessage(\r\n        ...,\r\n        MyActualMessage,\r\n        ...\r\n    ),\r\n    ...\r\n)\r\n```\r\n- but this message will only be decoded once on the receiving end so `OVM_L2CrossDomainMessenger` will be calling my contract with message `relayMessage(..., MyActualMessage, ...)` instead of `MyActualMessage`\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nI've tried it on Optimistic-Kovan where I successfully `replayMessage` on `OVM_L1CrossDomainMessenger` but the corresponding L2 message still fails.\r\n- [my contract](https://kovan.etherscan.io/address/0xd678895904733fffe9783ff04c4145f737122feb#code)\r\n  - the contract is the same on both L1 and L2\r\n- [L1 replayMessage tx](https://kovan.etherscan.io/tx/0x0fc797f46335a98a42207320fae0f314fef626d5b08d1fb841d11cbde073f22d)\r\n- [corresponding L2 message](https://kovan-optimistic.etherscan.io/tx/0xf1209facfe0868fdef1e717ccc3f5c0e20d9044a66526597db9a3117945caf44)\r\n\r\nMy contract has a switch so that I can control when L1->L2 message and L2->L1 message should fail. But the code is not verified so pasting the contract and transactions links here might not do much help.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nShould be able to replay cross domain message.\r\n\r\n",
